# OpenAI TTS Chrome Extension

## To-Do List for OpenAI TTS Chrome Extension

1. **Set Up Your Development Environment**
  - [x] Install Node.js and npm.

2. **Initialize Your Project**
  - [x] Create a project folder.
  - [x] Initialize npm with `npm init -y`.

3. **Install Necessary npm Packages**
  - [x] Install `dotenv` with `npm install dotenv`.
  - [x] Install `node-fetch` with `npm install node-fetch`.

4. **Create .env File**
  - [x] Create a `.env` file in the root of your project.
  - [ ] Add your OpenAI API key to the `.env` file.

5. **Create the Chrome Extension Manifest**
   - [x] Create `manifest.json` file in the project folder.

6. **Create Background Script**
   - [x] Create `background.js` file in the project folder.
   - [ ] Implement OpenAI TTS API request logic.

7. **Create Content Script**
   - [ ] Create `content.js` file in the project folder.
   - [ ] Implement logic to extract main content from the webpage.

8. **Create Popup UI**
   - [ ] Create `popup.html` file in the project folder.
   - [ ] Create `popup.js` file in the project folder.
   - [ ] Implement logic to control the extension and play TTS audio.

9. **Set Up Local Server**
   - [ ] Install Express and body-parser with `npm install express body-parser`.
   - [ ] Create `server.js` file in the project folder.
   - [ ] Implement TTS request handling using OpenAI API.

10. **Load the Extension in Chrome**
    - [ ] Go to `chrome://extensions/` in Chrome.
    - [ ] Enable "Developer mode".
    - [ ] Load your extension by selecting "Load unpacked" and choosing your project folder.

11. **Run the Local Server**
    - [ ] Start your local server with `node server.js`.

12. **Test the Extension**
    - [ ] Test the extension on different web pages.
    - [ ] Ensure it correctly extracts text and plays the TTS audio.

13. **Debug and Optimize**
    - [ ] Use Chrome Developer Tools to debug any issues.
    - [ ] Improve text extraction and implement word highlighting.

14. **Final Touches**
    - [ ] Add icons and improve the UI.
    - [ ] Document your code and create a README file explaining how to install and use the extension.

15. **Optional: Publish the Extension**
    - [ ] Follow the guide to publish your extension to the Chrome Web Store.

### Resources

- [OpenAI Text-to-Speech Documentation](https://platform.openai.com/docs/guides/text-to-speech?lang=node)
- [Chrome Extension Documentation](https://developer.chrome.com/docs/extensions/mv3/getstarted/)
